    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener>Dear Sir</opener>

                <p><persName ref="pe0139">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Lightfootâ€™s</persName>
                    <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0231">Flora scotica</title></bibl> is so near
                    publication, that I would advise any bookseller you chuse to favor to apply to
                    <persName ref="pe0026">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> White</persName> for any
                    number of copies He chuses for I imagine it will be a popular Book. <persName ref="pe0026">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> White</persName> has the sale of it so
                    the contract must be made with him. I continue here about 3 weeks; &amp; shall
                    be glad to hear from you.</p>
                <closer>I am <lb/><salute>D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sir <lb/>Y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> most obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed>
                <dateline><placeName ref="pl0692">Harrowgate</placeName>
                    <lb/><placeName ref="pl0770">Yorkshire</placeName>
                    <lb/>May 20<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1777.</dateline></closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Pray put the inclosed into the Post.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><address>
                        <addrLine>To</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> George Paton</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Custom house</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Edinburgh.</addrLine>
                    </address></p>
            </div>
